    {'id':'y3-t1-w5-l1','year':'Y3','term':'T1',     'week':5,'weekLesson':1,     'sequence':'Revisit','lesson':'Lesson 13',     'focus':'the use of apostrophes for',     'explanation':"Apostrophes are used in two main ways: to show possession (the cat's whiskers) and to mark missing letters in contractions (don't, I'm, it's). Be careful not to confuse it's (it is) with its (belonging to it) — its does not need an apostrophe.",     'hlWords':["don't", "can't", "it's", "girl's", "dog's", "won't", "I'm", "they're", "child's", "teacher's"]},
