    {'id':'y4-t5-w4-l1','year':'Y4','term':'T5',     'week':4,'weekLesson':1,     'sequence':'Sequence 8','lesson':'Lesson 1',     'focus':'when the root word ends in e, we remove the e before applying the…',     'explanation':'When a verb ends in a silent e, remove the e before adding the suffix -ation (invite → invitation, admire → admiration). For most other verbs, simply add -ation (expect → expectation, present → presentation). The -ation suffix always makes the /ay-shun/ sound.',     'hlWords':['presentation', 'formation', 'relaxation', 'expectation', 'adaptation', 'foundation', 'invitation', 'decoration', 'confirmation', 'installation']},
