    {'id':'y4-t5-w5-l1','year':'Y4','term':'T5',     'week':5,'weekLesson':1,     'sequence':'Sequence 9','lesson':'Lesson 1',     'focus':'all of the words contain the ou grapheme',     'explanation':"The letters 'ou' can represent several different sounds. They most commonly make the /ow/ sound (out, shout, cloud) but can also make the /oo/ sound (you, through), the short /u/ sound (country, young, touch) or the /or/ sound (four, pour, court). These different sounds just have to be learned for each word.",     'hlWords':['shout', 'young', 'four', 'country', 'out', 'cloud', 'touch', 'pour', 'you', 'ground']},
