    {'id':'y4-t6-w1-l1','year':'Y4','term':'T6',     'week':1,'weekLesson':1,     'sequence':'Sequence 10','lesson':'Lesson 1',     'focus':'gue grapheme produces the g sound and the que grapheme produces the…',     'explanation':"The letter string 'gue' at the end of a word makes the /g/ sound — the u prevents the g from making the /j/ sound (league, vague, dialogue). The letter string 'que' makes the /k/ sound (unique, antique, critique). Both spellings come from French loanwords and the final e is silent.",     'hlWords':['league', 'unique', 'antique', 'vague', 'dialogue', 'mosque', 'fatigue', 'technique', 'critique', 'catalogue']},
